    "teaserEn": "A small Melbourne food memory: the oysters and black truffle toast at Queen Victoria Market were both very good, in the direct, uncomplicated way that makes a market morning stay with me.",
    "bodyEn": "Queen Victoria Market in Melbourne gave me one of those small food memories that does not need much explanation.\n\nThe oysters were fresh, cold, and clean in that simple market way. They did not feel dressed up; they were just good. The black truffle toast was also unexpectedly satisfying: warm, rich, fragrant, and direct.\n\nIt was not a grand meal, and maybe that is why I remember it clearly. Sometimes a place stays with me through one very specific bite: standing around a market, eating something simple, and feeling that the day has already become better."
